diet have been relatively slight. Although smoking practice has halved in some 
populations, its prevalence is now rising in the young. The extent of physical 
activity is low, compared with that in the past, and may even be decreasing in 
the young. With the general ageing of populations, the near absence of strong 
encouragement from the state, and individuals' general failure to reduce risk 
factors significantly, the chances of decreases in the incidence of CHD appear 
remote.

